Movie: Lupin the Third: Sweet Lost Night

Review: Lon chaney is amazing as always, but i think The Unknown it’s a better movie of this genre. That said, this is another example of an specific trope i hate, the one where a woman (usually a spy) gives up her ideals and motivation bc she fell in love with the protagonist (and most of the time it doesn’t even makes sense for her to like him, like in this movie).
